                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/203: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Mission’s No. 20 of November 25, 6 p.m. has just been received in corrected
                    form. You may support in appropriate manner <pb facs="0561" n="447"
                        xml:id="pg_447"/> plea on humanitarian grounds for the release of Ottoman
                    Greek males in view of the defenceless position in which refugee women and
                    children are left in the absence of their natural protectors. Further ground for
                    support may be found in the large demand which the existing situation creates
                    for American generosity.</p>
                <p>The matter of a possible loan would call for further consideration should there
                    be a definite request to bankers. The Department does not see how it will alter
                    present state of helplessness to have Greek supervision of relief money
                    expenditure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
